**Locating Files**

One of the initial steps in working with game assets involves locating the game files for any installed game. This process can vary depending on the platform and distribution method of the game. A combination of methods such as Windows Registry entries, Game Store applications, or specific folders within the game directory can aid in identifying the locations of installed games and their associated files. Understanding how to effectively navigate these different avenues for locating game files is crucial for accessing and manipulating game assets accurately. By mastering the techniques for locating game files, digital creators can streamline their workflow and enhance their ability to work with game assets efficiently.